Agency in Linear FPS


•  Agency – Power to accomplish expected result with given action 
–  Not necessarily ability to alter grand scheme/direction of game 
•	 Linear plot progression 
–	 Player somewhat limited by designer’s plot (more formal constraints) 
–	 Alignment of player desire and narrative limits required 
In a game with a linear plot, player agency becomes a short term 
version with an emphasis on material constraints. 
–	 Short term – actions have immediate effects 
–	 Material Constraints – determine what actions are possible 

