Replayability of Games


•	

•	 Mateas and Stern – agency cannot be achieved when 
watching/playing a game for the second time (unrealistic formal 
constraints) 
In terms of player’s narrative, it is nearly impossible to play the same 
game twice. Games with branching plots present so many different 
possibilities that they constitute separate games. I will try to apply 
Mateas and Stern to a linear FPS. 
•	 Agency – more fully achieved on the second playthrough 
–	 Better understanding of material constraints (abilities and puzzles) 
–	 Formal Constraints – not a major factor for agency in this case 

