Conclusion


•	 Games in the Half-Life Series provide model examples 
of Jenkins’ embedded and enacted narratives. 
•	 The difference between story in other media and 
narrative in games gives players the flexibility to co-
author the game along with the designers. 
•	 As a result, agency in Half-Life and other linear games is 
achieved in the short term with an emphasis on material 
constraints. 
•	 The importance of co-authorship and agency in game 
design underscores the fundamental importance of the 
player to games themselves. 

